<div class="zm-item-answer-detail">
<div class="zm-item-answer-author-info">
<h3 class="zm-item-answer-author-wrap">


<a data-tip="p$t$fu-er" href="/people/fu-er">负二</a>，<strong title="《时间中的侦探》作者" class="zu-question-my-bio">《时间中的侦探》作者</strong>

</h3>
<a href="javascript:;" name="collapse" class="collapse meta-item zg-right"><i class="z-icon-fold"></i>收起</a>
</div>
<div class="zm-item-vote-info " data-votecount="24">

<span class="voters">
<span class="user-block"><a data-tip="p$t$miachen" href="http://www.zhihu.com/people/miachen" class="zg-link" title="陈情报">陈情报</a>、</span><span class="user-block"><a data-tip="p$t$lilililililith" href="http://www.zhihu.com/people/lilililililith" class="zg-link" title="莉斯">莉斯</a>、</span><span class="user-block"><a data-tip="p$t$jin-zhao-58" href="http://www.zhihu.com/people/jin-zhao-58" class="zg-link" title="今朝">今朝</a></span>
</span>


<a href="javascript:;" class="more"> 等人赞同</a>


</div>
<div class="zm-item-rich-text" data-resourceid="106205" data-action="/answer/content">

<div class="fixed-summary zm-editable-content clearfix"> 我见过最具实验性的写法是唐纳德·巴塞尔姆的《白雪公主》<br>那本书能从任何一页开始，以任何顺序阅读，到任何一页结束，你都不会觉得不对劲。<br>另外，卡尔维诺的《命运交叉的城堡》、帕维奇的《哈扎尔词典》，也都是现代小说结构探索中很有意思的案例。 


</div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
